[Name] IRQBalance
[Summary] irqbalance is a Linux* daemon that distributes interrupts over the processors and cores you have in your computer system.
[Description] The design goal of irqbalance is to do find a balance between power savings and optimal performance. To a large degree, the work irqbalance does is invisible to you; if irqbalance performs its job right, nobody will ever notice it's there or want to turn it off. 
[License] GNU GPL/v2
[Homepage] http://irqbalance.org/
